\c 11
\s1 TUHAN mengirim api karena orang Israel menggerutu
\p
\v 1 Pada suatu hari orang Israel menggerutu kepada TUHAN tentang pengalaman buruk yang menimpa mereka. Karena itu, TUHAN menjadi marah dan mendatangkan api di atas perkemahan orang Israel dan menghanguskan sebagian dari perkemahan mereka.
\p
\v 2 Orang Israel berseru minta tolong kepada Musa. Lalu Musa berdoa kepada TUHAN, dan api itu padam.
\p
\v 3 Itu sebabnya tempat itu dinamai Tabera— karena api TUHAN menyala-nyala di antara mereka.
\s1 Musa memilih 70 orang pemimpin
\p
\v 4 Dalam perjalanan orang Israel, ada juga sekelompok orang asing yang ikut bersama mereka. Sekelompok orang itu ingin sekali makan daging. Karena itu, orang Israel juga mulai mengeluh dengan berkata, “Ah, kami mau makan makanan yang lebih [enak//baik]!”
\p Then some troublemakers from other people-groups \add who weretraveling\add* with the Israelis began to want better food. And \add when they startedcomplaining\add* the Israeli people also started to complain.
\v 5 Mereka berkata, “Seandainya kami punya daging [di sini] untuk kami makan!
\v 6 Kami ingat akan ikan yang kami makan di Mesir dengan gratis, mentimun dan semangka, daun bawang, bawang merah dan bawang putih. Tetapi sekarang di sini kami tidak ada makanan untuk kami makan, selain manna.We remember the fish that we ate while we were in Egypt, fish that was given to us without ◄cost/asking us to pay for it►.And we had all the cucumbers, melons, leeks, onions, and garlic \add that wewanted\add*. But now we do not have any desire to eat, because all we have to eat is this manna!”
\p
\v 7 Manna itu seperti biji ketumbar, warnanya putih kekuning-kuningan.
\p The manna resembled small white seeds.
\v 8 Setiap pagi orang Israel berjalan keluar untuk mengumpulkan manna. Kemudian mereka menggiling manna itu dengan batu gilingan atau menumbuknya dalam lesung dan merebusnya dalam periuk. Lalu membuatnya menjadi roti bundar yang rasanya seperti kue yang dipanggang dengan minyak zaitun.\add Each morning\add* the people would go out and gather some\add from the surface of the ground\add*. Then they made flour by grinding it or pounding it with stones. Then they\add added water and\add* boiled it in a pot, or they made flat cakes with it\add and baked them\add*. The cakes tasted like bread that was baked with\add olive\add* oil.
\v 9 Pada malam hari, manna itu turun di tempat perkemahan bersamaan dengan embun.
\p Each night the manna came down on their ground where their tents were, like dew\add from the sky\add*.
\p
\v 10 Ketika Musa mendengar orang Israel itu [menangis sambil menggerutu//meratap//menggerutu, sambil berdiri berkelompok-kelompok di pintu kemah mereka, maka marahlah TUHAN dan Musa sangat sedih.
\p Moses/I heard all the Israeli people complaining as they were standing in the entrances of their tents. Yahweh became very angry, and Moses/I was also very perturbed.
\v 11 Lalu Musa berbicara kepada TUHAN, "Mengapa Engkau menyusahkan aku, dengan memilih hamba-Mu ini untuk menanggung beban suatu bangsa seperti mereka ini?
\p He/I \add went into the Sacred Tent and\add* asked Yahweh, “Why have you brought this trouble me me, your servant [RHQ]? Act mercifully to me! What wrong have I done, with the result that you have appointed me to take care of all of these people [RHQ]?
\v 12 Memangnya saya ini ayah mereka?! Mengapa Engkau menyuruh saya mengasuh mereka terus-menerus sepanjang perjalanan menuju ke tanah yang Engkau janjikan kepada nenek moyang mereka?!◄I am not their father./Am I their father?► [RHQ] Why have you told me to take care of them like a woman carries around her baby and ◄nurses it/gives it her milk► [MET, RHQ]? How can I take them to the land that you promised to give to our ancestors [RHQ]?
\v 13 Dari manakah hamba-Mu ini dapat memperoleh daging untuk diberikan kepada semua orang ini?! Mereka terus-menerus merengek meminta daging untuk mereka makan! Where can I get meat to feed all these people? They keep complaining to me, saying, ‘Give us some meat to eat!’
\v 14 Saya tidak sanggup lagi menanggung beban atas seluruh bangsa ini seorang diri, terlalu berat bagiku.I cannot carry all these people's burdens by myself! \add They are like a heavy load tome\add* [MET], and I cannot carry this very heavy load anymore.
\v 15 Kalau Engkau memperlakukan saya seperti ini, lebih baik Engkau membunuh saya sekarang juga!"If you intend to act like this toward me, kill me now. If you are really concerned about me, be kind to me and\add kill me to\add* end my misery \add of trying to take care ofthem\add*!”
\p
\v 16 Lalu TUHAN berbicara kepada Musa, "Kumpulkanlah 70 orang tua-tua Israel yang diakui sebagai pemimpin bangsa, dan bawalah mereka di hadapan-Ku, di dalam Rumah-Ku!serta mintalah mereka berdiri di sampingmu.
\p Then Yahweh said to Moses/me, “Summon seventy men whom you know are leaders among the Israeli people. Tell them to stand with you in front of the Sacred Tent.
\p
\v 17 Aku akan turun untuk berbicara denganmu di tempat itu. Sebagian dari kuasa yang sudah Aku berikan kepadamu, akan Aku berikan kepada mereka, supaya mereka dapat membantumu memikul tanggung jawab atas bangsa ini. Dengan demikian, kamu tidak lagi memikul tanggung jawab ini seorang diri.
\p I will come down and talk with you there. Then I will take some of\add the power of\add* my Spirit that you have, and I will put \add thatpower\add* on them also. They will help you to take care of some of the things that the people are concerned about, in order that you will not need to do it alone.
\p
\v 18 Katakanlah kepada seluruh orang Israel, "Sucikanlah dirimu karena besok kalian akan makan daging. TUHAN sudah mendengar kalian menangis dan mengeluh karena kalian ingin makan daging dan juga kalian lebih memilih tinggal di Mesir. Karena itu, TUHAN akan memberi kalian daging untuk kalian makan.Furthermore, say to the people, ‘Make yourselves acceptable to me, and tomorrow you will have meat to eat. You were complaining, and Yahweh heard you when you were saying, “We want some meat to eat. We had better food in Egypt!” Now Yahweh will give you some meat, and you will eat it.
\v 19 Kalian akan memakan daging itu tidak hanya 1 atau 2 hari, atau hanya 5 hari, 10 atau 20 hari,You will eat meat not only for one or two days, or only for five or ten or twenty days.
\v 20 melainkan kalian akan makan setiap hari selama 1 bulan sampai kalian menjadi sakit dan muntah-muntah karena makan daging. Hal itu akan terjadi karena, kalian menolak TUHAN yang ada bersama kalian dan juga karena kalian masih merindukan Mesir.\add You will eat meat every day\add* for one month, and then you will loathe/despise it, and it will cause you to wantto vomit. \add This will happen\add* because you have rejected Yahweh who is here among you, and you have wailed in hispresence, saying “We \add would have had better food to eat\add* if we had not left Egypt [RHQ].” ’ ”
\p
\v 21 Tetapi Musa menjawab TUHAN, kaum pria saja ada 600.000 orang, belum lagi kaum wanita dan anak-anak. Namun Engkau menjanjikan memberikan daging kepada mereka setiap hari selama sebulan.But Moses/I replied to Yahweh, “There are six hundred thousand men\add plus women and children\add* here with me, so ◄\add why\add* do you say ‘I will give them plenty of meat every day for a month!’?/it is ridiculous for you to say ‘I will give them plenty of meat every day for a month!’► [RHQ]
\v 22 Sekalipun kami memotong semua domba dan sapi kami, bahkan kami menangkap semua ikan di laut untuk diberikan kepada mereka, itu semua tidak akan pernah cukup!"Even if we killed all the sheep and cattle, that would not [RHQ] be enough\add to provide meat for all of them\add*! Even if we caught all the fish in the sea\add and gave it to them\add*, that would not be enough [RHQ]!”
\v 23 Lalu TUHAN berbicara kepada Musa, "Apakah kuasa-Ku terbatas? Sekarang, lihatlah apakah perkataan-Ku akan terjadi atau tidak."But Yahweh said to Moses/me, “Do you think that I [SYN] have no power? You will now see if I can do what I say I will do.”
\p
\v 24 Lalu Musa keluar dan menyampaikan perkataan TUHAN kepada seluruh orang Israel. Dia juga mengumpulkan 70 orang tua-tua Israel dan meminta mereka berdiri di sekeliling Rumah TUHAN.So Moses/I went out \add from the Sacred Tent\add* and told the people what Yahweh had said. Then he/I gathered together the seventy leaders and told them to stand around the Sacred Tent.
\p
\v 25 Kemudian TUHAN turun dalam awan dan berbicara kepada Musa. TUHAN mengambil sebagian Roh yang ada pada Musa dan memberikannya kepada ke 70 tua-tua Israel itu. Setelah Roh-Nya turun ke atas mereka, maka para tua-tua itu bernubuat, namun hanya sekali itu saja mereka bernubuat. Then the Yahweh came down in the cloud \add that was above thetent\add* and spoke to Moses/me. He took some of \add the power of\add* the Spirit that he had given to Moses/me and gave it to the seventy leaders. By means of the power of the Spirit within them, they ◄prophesied/spoke messages that Yahweh gave them►, but they did that only once.
\p
\v 26 Dari 70 tua-tua Israel yang tercatat namanya, ada 2 orang yang tetap tinggal di perkemahannya, Eldad dan Medad yang tidak ikut ke Rumah TUHAN. Ketika Roh turun ke atas mereka, mereka berdua bernubuat seperti nabi.Two of the leaders whom Moses/I appointed, Eldad and Medad, were not there when the rest of them gathered together. Theyhad not left \add their tents\add* to go and stand around the Sacred Tent. But Yahweh's Spirit came on them also, and they started to ◄prophesy/speak messages from Yahweh►.
\v 27 Kemudian seorang pemuda berlari untuk memberitahukan hal itu kepada Musa, "Eldad dan Medad bernubuat seperti nabi diperkemahannya."So a young man ran and told Moses/me, “Eldad and Medad are prophesying where all their tents are!”
\p
\v 28 Yosua, anak dari Nun yang membantu Musa sejak dari masa mudanya berbicara kepada Musa, "Bapak berhentikanlah mereka!"
\p Joshua, who had helped Moses/me since he was a young man, said, “Sir, tell them to stop doing that!”
\p
\v 29 Tetapi Musa menjawab, "Apakah kamu khawatir, mereka menyaingi aku? Saya malah berharap supaya TUHAN mèmberikan Roh-Nya kepada semua orang Israel untuk menjadi nabi!"But Moses/I replied, “◄Are you worried that they might injure my reputation/Do you think that I want to be the only one who prophesies► [RHQ]? I wish that all Yahweh's people could ◄prophesy/speak messages from Yahweh►. I wish that Yahweh would give the power of his Spirit to all of them!”
\v 30 Kemudian Musa kembali ke perkemahan bersama ke 70 orang tua-tua Israel itu.Then Moses/I and all the leaders went back to their/our tents.
\p
\v 31 Lalu TUHAN mendatangkan angin dari laut yang membawa banyak sekali burung puyuh di sekeliling perkemahan. Burung puyuh itu beterbangan rendah di sekitar perkemahan, kira-kira 1 meter di atas permukaan tanah dan di sekeliling perkemahan sejauh beberapa kilometer.
\p Then Yahweh sent a strong wind from the sea. It blew quail into the area all around the camp,\add and caused the quail to fall onto the ground\add*. They were piled up on the ground about ◄3 feet/1 meter► high!
\p
\v 32 Orang Israel keluar untuk menangkap burung puyuh itu sepanjang hari, sepanjang malam dan sepanjang hari berikutnya mereka bersemangat menangkapnya tidak kurang dari 1000 kg. Burung-burung puyuh yang sudah ditangkap itu, mereka jemur di sekeliling perkemahan.So the people went out and gathered up the quail all that day, and all that night, and all of the following day.\add It seemed as though\add* everyone gathered at least fifty bushels! They spread the quail out on the ground all around thecamp, \add so that the quail would lose their moisture\add*.
\v 33 Sementara masih banyak daging burung puyuh untuk dimakan, TUHAN sangat marah kepada orang Israel dan mendatangkan suatu wabah penyakit di antara mereka dan banyak orang yang meninggal.\add Then they cooked them and started to eat them\add*. But while they were still eating the meat [MTY], Yahweh\add showed that he\add* was very angry with them. He sent a severe plague/sickness on them,\add and many people died\add*.
\v 34 Itu sebabnya, tempat itu dinamai 'Kibrot Hatawa' karena di tempat itu dikuburkan orang-orang yang meninggal karena [rakus//bernafsu] makan daging.The people who died and were buried were the ones who had said they wanted to eat meat\add like they had formerly eaten in Egypt\add*. So they called that place Kibroth-Hattaavah,\add which means\add* '\add graves of those who craved\add*.'
\p
\v 35 Dari Kibrot Hatawa, orang Israel [melanjutkan perjalanan//pindah] ke daerah Hazerot dan mereka berkemah di sana untuk sementara waktu.From there, the Israelis continued walking \add east\add* until they arrived at Hazeroth\add town\add*, where they stopped and stayed \add for a long time\add*.